race.comment: SOUTHERN CHARM (11) wasn't disgraced in Saturday metro grade last time out and should find this assignment much more to her liking. Is yet to miss a drum in three spins around this circuit and should be right there when the judge calls a halt. MISHANI CROWN (10) has put back-to-back wins together and it's hard to knock mares in form. Gets 1.5kg off with the claim and can bring up the hat-trick here. BEEN A SECRET (12) has remarkably hit the top-five at her past 20 starts and doesn't know how to put in a poor one. Don't dismiss lightly. TREPORTI (4) has placed two of three over this track and trip and is usually thereabouts. In the mix. DIANA'S AFFAIR (7) strips fitter second-up, draws the inside alley and gets 3kg off. Ticks a few boxes.
